content.description: Climb  straight up the left side of the face without using the right portion of the  cracked boulder. Crouch start on the waist high slopey ledges on the left and right. Using the right portion of the boulder drops the problem down to a V0-V1. A fun problem either way!
content.location: On the cracked, north side of the Que Luna boulder 100 ft south of the sanctuary/ forest parking area.

content.description: Climb the slab along the left side of the boulder using good edges. Great warmup.
content.location: The smallest of the boulders in the trio. Look for the clean, slabby face past The Layback.

content.description: Climb the tall face using the left arete and the small crack up high. Super fun, but don't fall off the top.
content.protection: Highball. Landing is good, you'll want pads.
content.location: To the right and around the corner from The Layback. Easy downclimb on the back.

content.description: Start crouched on a right facing side pull and a low left flake, stab to a crimp on a slopey shelf into a triangle pinch finish straight up with an easy top out.
content.location: the left side of the Que Luna Boulder

content.description: Start crouched using a right-facing edge and work your way up the overhung arete. The finish is tricky, bring pads.
content.location: On the downhill face of the boulder on the right when you arrive at the Que Luna trio. Look for the overhanging arete and "built-up" landing.

content.description:
Center-right of the slab face of the eastern-most boulder in the Que Luna trio.

To start, use good ledges about shin-level for feet, hands in the bottom cracks (about shoulder level). Ascend the slab face using a combination of horizontal cracks and widely-spaced knobs, trusting your feet along the face. Top out with a mantel, then walk down and towards Que Luna boulder, passing behind, to descend.

Stay towards the center; a variation tackles the arete to the right.

Crux is the second half of the problem, where hand and foot options begin to space out.

A fun problem tucked away from the trail.

FA with Samuel Maxwell and Liliya Shtikel, 01/31/2015
content.location:
Located in the Clearcut on the slab eastern boulder in the Que Luna trio.

The approach and landing area can be muddy

To get there: descend the trail from The Forest/Sanctuary area located on the west side of the "East Parking Lot". Walk down the trail towards Fraggle Rock. The Que Luna trio is located south of the trail, off in the brush about 25 feet. The trail turn-off is about halfway between Fraggle Rock and the East Parking Lot/The Sanctuary (just south of Warm Up Boulder)

content.description: Climb the right side of the huge flake on the largest boulder in the Que Luna trio. The start is the crux but it still isn't a gimme above.
content.location: Head to the Que Luna trio, this is likely the first line you will see on the huge boulder. Easy downclimb on the backside. There is a bolt on top as well.
